modules.description: Provides functions to construct and modify configuration objects for HTML elements, adding classes and attributes to tables, text, rows, and columns. Works with lists of class names and specific attribute types from the Tyxml library. Used to control the rendering of table structures and collapsible tree summaries in HTML output.

Provides functions to render structured data such as boxes, lists, and arrays in text and HTML formats, with support for nested elements. Operates on custom data types representing layout and content, including recursive structures. Used to generate formatted output for debugging, documentation, or user interfaces.

Injects HTML into a box using native handling, focusing on table and collapsible structure rendering. It manages configuration objects with Tyxml attributes and class lists, enabling customization of tables, rows, columns, and text elements. Operations include adding classes, setting attributes, and modifying layout properties. Examples include generating styled tables with collapsible sections or dynamically adjusting element attributes.
